&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;The confusion matrix is very helpful to understand the details of our classifiers performance however we still need some metrics to interpret more directly to choose the best model&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;So in this notebook we will talk about the metrics like &lt;strong&gt;sensitivity (recall), specifity, precision and F1 score&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;These metrics can be computed from a confusion matrix and are more efficient to choose the best model. &lt;/li&gt;
